snippet.textDisplay: How in God's green earth is Phil Jones, Jesse Lingard, Luke Shaw, Ashley Young, Andreas Pereira, Eric Bailly, Marcos Rojo, Nemanja Matic, and Juan Mata still at Manchester United...why is it that Ole and the board somehow retain players that are either...1) not good enough, 2) past their prime, and 3) injury prone, can someone please explain why? As Man Utd fans we need to ask ourselves would any of these players even start for teams like Liverpool, Man City, Chelsea or Spurs? If Ole believes in this team with these players,  than he is delusional, these are the same players that fail LVG, and Mourinho and they are doing it again with Ole, how on earth is this rebuild ever gonna take off if we keep extending contracts to players that should not even be a the club anymore, but most importantly how in the hell are we ever gonna rebuild if we don't buy top quality players...players like James Maddison, Timo Werner, Saul Niguez, Fabian Ruiz, Donny van de beek, Bruno Fernandes, Jadon Sancho, Denis Zakaria, Jose Gaya, there's so much talent out there go and get them, stop wasting time because time waits for no one, Manchester United will never be back to glory days if we keep wasting time, we live in times of modern football and money talks period, it's time for the board, Ed or whoever is in charge of transfers to be aggressive and get players in, enough is enough

snippet.textDisplay: Time for some perspective. During 1988-89 and 1989-90, United finished 11th and 13th during the third and fourth season under a certain Alex Ferguson. We’re currently 5th in the league and we have a chance of top 4/winning Europa and maybe the FA Cup (League Cup is basically gone now). Fergie also didn’t win a trophy until 1990. I’m sick of fans not understanding that we’re going through a similar period now (whether we like it or not) and actually we’re better now than then. We have had many disappointing games this season but the current squad is not good enough and needs improving. Ole has already got rid of some deadwood and brought in promising players. He needs longer, at least until the end of this season and see who he brings in in the summer. All this about ‘we can’t accept mediocrity’ well it’s as simple as that is it. Ole is supposed to wave his magic wand is he? Just fucking get behind the man and trust the process. I will keep on saying it, I don’t care.
